snippet.textDisplay:
5:12
The vibe changes totally.. 
I call it sound of hope. Heavy lyrics and deep poetry is coming. 

Such a beautiful composition. 
I really miss coke studio. 

I have created a playlist with songs of India. And this is a very important song in that playlist. After listening Ravish Kumar's emotional and moving speech on international mother's language day, I stared listing bhojpuri songs.. mainly chairi, kajri and other folks. 
Such a beautiful language Bhojpuri is.. it's in fact the fastest growing language in the whole world. I like to listen more bhojpuri songs like this..

snippet.textDisplay:
the first song "Gawahi dhora pitati ki neh na kariyo koi" is originally a meera bai creation. she wrote " Gawahi dhora pitati ki sneh kare na koi , ki pyar kare na koi"
It describes the peeda (pain) she feels when she is getting married to Rana because she has already given her heart to Krishna. While her sakhis (friends) around her are celebrating her marriage to Rana, her soul is crying out "ki neh kare na koi"
